    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> ras el hanout</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until the onion has caramelised</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632741584319-x200.jpg",
